---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <section class="projects">
    <h2 class="projects-title">Projects</h2>
    <div class="project-grid">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/product-management-angular"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Product-Management-Angular</h3>
          <p>
            This project is a full-stack web application that allows users to
            add, delete, and edit products. It consists of a frontend built with
            Angular and SCSS, and a backend built with Express.js.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/money-tracker-app"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Money Tracker</h3>
          <p>
            Track your finances easily with Vue.js and TypeScript. Dexie.js
            powers seamless storage (indexed db) integration, keeping your data
            private on browser without needing a backend. Simplifies managing
            income and expenses with a user-friendly interface to stay on top of
            your financial health.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/python-task-scheduling"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Python-Task-Scheduling</h3>
          <p>
            This project is designed to facilitate efficient task scheduling and
            management for backend operations using Python. By leveraging
            Celery, a powerful distributed task queue, and RabbitMQ, a robust
            message broker, the system ensures reliable execution of
            asynchronous tasks. Docker is utilized to containerize the
            application, providing a consistent and reproducible environment for
            deployment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/watchup"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>WatchUp</h3>
          <p>
            App for discovering trending movies and managing your personal
            watchlist. Developed using TMDB API and React.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/expressjs-jwt-auth"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>API with JWT Authentication (Express.js)</h3>
          <p>
            This project uses Express.js, and for authentication, it employs JWT
            (JSON Web Token). Users log in with their credentials, and if
            verified, they get this special token. With it, they can access
            protected parts of the app without logging in repeatedly. Lastly,
            users can log in and out. Logging in grants access, while logging
            out invalidates the token, ensuring security.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/chatapp-websocket-fullstack"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Chat App (Websocket - Socket.IO)</h3>
          <p>
            A dynamic chat application seamlessly integrating WebSocket
            technology with the power and flexibility of Vue.js.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/express-ddos-protection"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Express-DDOS-Protection</h3>
          <p>
            A secure web application using Express.js, implementing Helmet for
            enhanced security headers, rate limiting to mitigate potential DDoS
            attacks, and IP filtering for access control.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/file-upload-fullstack"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>File Upload Full Stack (MongoDB - Mongoose)</h3>
          <p>
            This project is a file upload service built using Node.js with
            Express. It provides functionality for users to upload image files
            (PNG, JPEG, JPG, GIF) to a MongoDB database.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/jwt-full-stack"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Full-stack Web App with JWT Authentication</h3>
          <p>
            JWT Authentication Mono Repo Project is a comprehensive solution for
            secure user authentication, encompassing both frontend and backend
            components within a single repository. Utilizing JSON Web Tokens
            (JWT), ensuring data privacy and integrity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/python-qr"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Python-QR</h3>
          <p>
            A Python-based QR code generator that converts text, image or vcards
            into QR codes, enabling easy data sharing and quick access through
            scanning.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/image-resizing"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Image Resizing (MongoDB - Mongoose)</h3>
          <p>
            This project is a Node.js application using Express for handling
            image uploads, resizing them using Sharp, and storing metadata in
            MongoDB. Users can upload images, specifying desired dimensions.
            Resized images are saved locally, and their metadata is stored in
            the database. Users can list all stored images, and are allowed to
            download images by ID.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/expressjs-mongodb-vuejs"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Note App (MongoDB - Mongoose)</h3>
          <p>
            A note-taking application built with a backend and a frontend.
            Utilizing MongoDB and Mongoose for robust data management,
            Express.js for a flexible and efficient server, and Vue.js for a
            dynamic and user-friendly interface.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/expressjs-postgresql-vuejs"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Note App (PostgreSQL - Sequelize)</h3>
          <p>
            This project is a web-based note-taking application built with a
            modern technology stack: Backend: Nodejs, Express.js, PostgreSQL
            Frontend: Vue.js, Typescript Features: Users can create, edit, and
            delete notes. Notes are stored in a PostgreSQL database. This
            project demonstrates full-stack development skills, integrating a
            backend with a dynamic frontend.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/OAuth"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>OAuth Login Using Google, Github (MongoDB - Mongoose)</h3>
          <p>
            Full-stack application with Google and GitHub OAuth authentication,
            using JWT, MongoDB, Express.js, and Passport.js for the backend, and
            Vite, Vue, and TypeScript for the frontend.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/python-url-shortener"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Python-URL-Shortener</h3>
          <p>
            This project is a Flask-based web application that allows users to
            generate short URLs from long ones. Built with Python, it provides a
            simple and efficient way to create and manage shortened links,
            making it easy to share and track URLs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/todolist-vue"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>TodoApp</h3>
          <p>
            App for creating todolist and managing current todos. Developed
            using Vite and Vue.js
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/onurkantarci/docker-project"
        class="project-card"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <div class="project-info">
          <h3>Vue-Express Docker Setup</h3>
          <p>
            A full-stack web app with a Vue.js frontend and an Express.js
            backend, both containerized using Docker for easy orchestration and
            seamless communication.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .projects {
    animation: fadeIn 500ms ease-in-out;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: 80%;
    font-size: 20px;
  }

  .projects-title {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .project-grid {
    display: grid;
    margin: 0 100px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 40px;
  }

  .project-card {
    background: #1e1e1f;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition:
      transform 0.3s ease,
      box-shadow 0.3s ease;
    text-decoration: none;
    position: relative;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .project-card::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3),
      rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)
    );
    z-index: 1;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s;
  }

  .project-card:hover {
    transform: scale(1.05) rotate(1deg);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
  }

  .project-card:hover::before {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .project-card img {
    border-bottom: 2px solid #2ac670;
    border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .project-info {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    padding: 15px;
  }

  .project-info h3 {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2ac670;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2ac670;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    height: 80px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .project-info p {
    color: #ddd;
    line-height: 1.6;
    flex-grow: 1;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .projects {
      max-width: 100%;
    }

    .project-grid {
      margin: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
